      {
        "id": 2493436,
        "name": "Elliot Steele",
        "username": "Elliot_Steele",
        "avatar_template": "/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/e/ec9cab/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2018-10-01T02:36:17.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"146128\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>thx Barry , will look to see if the Pouilly and Saint Veran are available locally\u2026<br>\nElliot: will also look for the Vire Clesse \u2026Am always looking for Macon whites that I haven\u2019t tried before \u2026</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Keep a look out for the Les Pierres Blanches, Cuvee Speciale, and V.V. bottlings. The first being my personal favorite. As far as aging goes I feel like they are best drunk between 4 and 8 years of age, but I haven\u2019t had any older examples to show me where they end up past that so I\u2019ll defer to someone else on that one.</p>",
